00:13:15.873 --> 00:13:19.893
And this is where we will make this moment, this choice where I can implant into my mucosa.

267
00:13:20.153 --> 00:13:25.393
We see that it seeks to adhere, to penetrate; there, it begins to send out...

268
00:13:25.393 --> 00:13:29.613
How do we say that? Acid.

269
00:13:30.073 --> 00:13:33.393
It's a bit... You see?

270
00:13:41.526 --> 00:13:44.426
There is a very significant metabolic activity.

271
00:13:47.026 --> 00:13:49.446
And now, everyone, please observe here,

272
00:13:49.586 --> 00:13:54.226
even gentlemen in the back, observe carefully.

273
00:14:02.779 --> 00:14:04.059
I am entering the mucosa.

274
00:14:04.179 --> 00:14:06.579
Eighth day, amniotic cavity.

275
00:14:06.759 --> 00:14:09.979
Here, we observe the emergence of pressure on the right, and pressure on the left.

276
00:14:10.259 --> 00:14:16.859
And this is what generates a pressure force

277
00:14:16.859 --> 00:14:17.479
located here.

278
00:14:18.419 --> 00:14:21.759
This is where this amniotic cavity will emerge.

279
00:14:22.519 --> 00:14:27.299
And it is there, within this embryoblast, at the moment this cavity forms,

280
00:14:27.599 --> 00:14:30.159
cells organize and orient themselves

281
00:14:30.273 --> 00:14:31.933
towards the amniotic cavity

282
00:14:31.933 --> 00:14:33.833
and cells that organize

283
00:14:33.833 --> 00:14:36.453
and orient themselves towards the vitelline cavity

284
00:14:36.453 --> 00:14:37.793
and this is where the appearance occurs

285
00:14:37.793 --> 00:14:39.633
of an epiblast and a hypoblast

286
00:14:39.633 --> 00:14:41.613
at this point, we already have a stage

287
00:14:41.613 --> 00:14:43.833
where we can identify a phase

288
00:14:43.833 --> 00:14:45.873
of a digestive nature

289
00:14:45.873 --> 00:14:48.113
and a digestive tissue

290
00:14:48.113 --> 00:14:50.093
that is developing, and a tissue

291
00:14:50.093 --> 00:14:51.733
